The United Nations mission in Iraq has reacted to the missile attacks on the country’s capital, targeted at US troops on Wednesday. UN said Iraq should not be made to “pay the price” in the escalating conflict between Tehran and Washington, according to Al Jazeera. In a statement, the UN mission said that the latest strikes “again violate Iraqi sovereignty.” “We call for urgent restraint and a resumption of dialogue. Iraq should not pay the price for external rivalries,” the statement added. Meanwlie, NATO has condemned the attacks and called on Iran to refrain from further violence. “Allies continue to consult & remain committed to our training mission in Iraq,” NATO chief, Jens Stoltenberg
wrote on Twitter. The calls came following Iranian missile attacks on US bases in Iraq by Iran on Wednesday.